)(240)+(2)(300) = 18780 $$;;$$\\begin{align} \\overline{x} = \\frac{\\sum x}{n} = \\frac{288}{9} = 32;\\\\ \\overline{t} = \\frac{\\sum t}{n} = \\frac{1185}{9} = 131.67\\end{align}$$;;Regression coefficient of x and t:;$$\\begin{align} \\beta_x = \\frac{\\sum xt - \\frac{\\sum x \\sum t}{n}}{\\sum t^2 - \\frac{(\\sum t)^2}{n}} ;\\\\ = \\frac{18780-\\frac{288 x 1185}{9}}{229725 - \\frac{1185^2}{9}};\\\\ = -0.2597\\end{align}$$;;$$\\therefore$$ Equation of the regression line of x on t:;$$\\begin{align} x - \\overline{x} = \\beta_x(t-\\overline{t});\\\\ \\Rightarrow x - 32 = -0.2597(t-131.67);\\\\ \\Rightarrow x = -0.2597t + 66.19;\\\\ \\Rightarrow x = -0.260t + 66.2 (from \\space GC) \\end{align}$$;;$$\\therefore$$ The corresponding estimated value of x when t = 300;$$ x_{300} = 66.1940-0.259701(300) = -11.72 = -11.7(3sf) $$;;$$\\therefore$$ Comment on the suitability of the model:;This estimated value of x is impossible because the concentration of the drug in the bloodstream cannot be negative. Besides, the curved nature of the graph suggests that a straight line is not a good model.;;The variable y is defined by y = ln x;(i);For the variables y and t, ;$$\\therefore$$ Let n be the sample size = 9;$$ \\sum y = \\ln 82 + \\ln 65 + \\ln 43 + \\ln 37 + \\ln 22 + \\ln 19 + \\ln 12 + \\ln 6 + \\ln 2 = ;26.959 $$;$$ \\sum y^2 = (\\ln 82)^2 + (\\ln 65)^2 + (\\ln 43)^2 + (\\ln 37)^2 + (\\ln 22)^2 + (\\ln 19)^2 + (\\ln 12)^2 + (\\ln 6)^2 + (\\ln 2)^2 = 92.120 $$;$$ \\sum t = 15+30+60+90+120+150+180+240+300=1185$$;$$ \\sum yt = (\\ln 82)(15) + (\\ln 65)(30) + (\\ln 43)(60) + (\\ln 37)(90) + (\\ln 22)(120) + (\\ln 19)(150) + (\\ln 12)(180) + (\\ln 6)(240) + (\\ln 2)(300) = 2639.8 $$;;$$\\therefore$$ The product moment correlation coefficient;$$\\begin{align} r = \\frac{\\sum yt - \\frac{\\sum y \\sum t}{n}}{\\sqrt{\\left(\\sum t^2 - \\frac{\\left(\\sum t\\right)^2}{n}\\right)\\left(\\sum y^2 - \\frac{\\left(\\sum y\\right)^2}{n}\\right)}} \\\\ = \\frac{2639.8 - \\frac{26.959 